# localpro-provider — Project Memory

## What it is
Expo Router provider-side mobile app (iOS, Android, Web) for **LocalPro Asia** (`localpro.asia`). Providers browse jobs, submit quotes, manage earnings, chat with clients, and maintain their profile/KYC.

## Stack
- **Expo SDK 54**, React 19, React Native 0.81.5, TypeScript (strict)
- **expo-router v6** — file-based routing, typed routes, React Compiler experiment enabled
- **TanStack Query** — all server state, caching, mutations
- **Zustand** — auth session (`auth-store`), notifications badge (`notification-store`), earnings cache (`earnings-store`)
- **Axios** (`src/api/client.ts`) — cookie sessions, CSRF on mutations, auto-refresh on 401
- **react-hook-form + zod** — all validated forms
- **react-native-sse** — SSE for live message threads
- **expo-secure-store** — only for training checkout session keys

## Key directories
| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/app/(auth)/` | Auth screens (login, register, phone, forgot/reset pw, verify email, pending approval) |
| `src/app/(app)/` | Main tab shell + all feature stacks |
| `src/api/` | Axios client + domain modules (auth, jobs, messages, quotes, earnings, etc.) |
| `src/stores/` | Zustand stores |
| `src/components/` | Shared UI (themed-text/view, icon, app-header, empty-state, loading-skeleton, status-chip) |
| `src/constants/theme.ts` | `Colors`, `Primary`, `Status`, spacing — single source of truth for styling |
| `src/hooks/` | `use-theme`, `use-color-scheme` (+ `.web` override) |

## Navigation structure
- Root `_layout.tsx` → `QueryClientProvider` + `AuthGuard` → `<Slot />`
- `(auth)` → Stack, no headers
- `(app)` → **5 visible tabs**: Home, Market(place), Jobs, Wallet, Chat
- Hidden tab entries (`href: null`) for: quotes, notifications, support, consultations, quote-templates, profile, loyalty, announcements, search

## Auth flow
1. Bootstrap: `GET /api/auth/me` → set user in Zustand or redirect to login
2. Role check: must be provider; `approvalStatus` must be `'approved'` (defaults to approved if missing from API)
3. Guard re-runs on `AppState → 'active'`
4. Session via HTTP-only cookies (`withCredentials: true`) — no manual token handling
5. CSRF: `GET /api/auth/csrf` → `x-csrf-token` header on all mutations
6. 401 → auto-refresh via `POST /api/auth/refresh`, failed refresh clears user

## Env vars
- `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL` — backend base URL (default `https://www.localpro.asia`)
- `EXPO_PUBLIC_APP_NAME` — app display name
- Path alias: `@/*` → `src/*`

